                        <br/><br/><br/><h2>文 献</h2><br><ol><br><li id="R1"><span class='au'>Weitzer, S. & Martinez, J.</span>: <span class="ti">The human RNA kinase hClp1 is active on 3’ transfer RNA exons and short interfering RNAs.</span> <span class='so'>Nature, 447, 222-226 (2007)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17495927" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R2"><span class='au'>de Vries, H, Ruegsegger, U., Hubner, W. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Human pre-mRNA cleavage factor II<sub>m</sub> contains homologs of yeast proteins and bridges two other cleavage factors.</span> <span class='so'>EMBO J., 19, 5895-5904 (2000)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11060040" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R3"><span class='au'>Paushkin, S. V., Patel, M., Furia, B. S. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Identification of a human endonuclease complex reveals a link between tRNA splicing and pre-mRNA 3’ end formation.</span> <span class='so'>Cell, 117, 311-321 (2004)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15109492" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R4"><span class='au'>Atkin, J. D., Scott, R. L., West, J. M. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Properties of slow- and fast-twitchmuscle fibres in amousemodel of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.</span> <span class='so'>Neuromuscul. Disord., 15, 377-388 (2005)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15833433" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R5"><span class='au'>Yamasaki, S., Ivanov, P., Hu, G. F. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Angiogenin cleaves tRNA and promotes stress-induced translational repression.</span> <span class='so'>J. Cell Biol., 185, 35-42 (2009)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19332886" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R6"><span class='au'>Lambert, P. F., Kashanchi, F., Radonovich, M. F. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Phosphorylation of p53 serine 15 increases interaction with CBP.</span> <span c